Note:
RUNA ANNOTATE TOOL - Annotation System Analyzer Entry Point

This file handles Runa annotation system processing and AI intent annotation management.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Scan Runa source files for existing annotation blocks (@Reasoning, @Implementation, etc.)
- Validate annotation block structure (matching @End closers, proper nesting)
- Report annotation coverage statistics per file and project
- Suggest missing annotation blocks for undocumented Processes and Types

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Runa annotate tool ensures comprehensive annotation coverage for AI-readability
- Proper annotation validation prevents malformed annotation blocks
- RunaAnnotate bridges user-facing CLI with compiler annotation parsing subsystem

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- AnnotationInfo type for representing a found annotation block
- scan_for_annotations to extract all annotation blocks from source
- validate_annotations to check for matching @End closers and proper structure
- report_annotation_coverage to display coverage statistics
- suggest_missing_annotations to identify unannotated Processes and Types
- run_annotate as the top-level entry point

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/file_utils.runa for file read operations
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa for memory allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa for arena-scoped allocation
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/file_utils.runa" as FileUtils
Import "compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa" as MemoryUtils
Import "compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa" as ArenaUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotate Tool Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant ANNOTATE_TOOL_VERSION as Integer is 1
Constant ANNOTATE_TOOL_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant ANNOTATE_TOOL_FAILURE as Integer is 1
Constant ANNOTATE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS as Integer is 2
Constant ANNOTATE_TOOL_ISSUES_FOUND as Integer is 3

Note: Annotation type identifiers
Constant ANNOT_REASONING as Integer is 1
Constant ANNOT_IMPLEMENTATION as Integer is 2
Constant ANNOT_PERFORMANCE_HINTS as Integer is 3
Constant ANNOT_SECURITY_SCOPE as Integer is 4
Constant ANNOT_TEST_CASES as Integer is 5
Constant ANNOT_UNKNOWN as Integer is 0

Note: AnnotationInfo memory layout (48 bytes):
Note: offset  0: annot_type (8 bytes) - Annotation type (ANNOT_*)
Note: offset  8: start_line (8 bytes) - Line number where annotation block starts
Note: offset 16: end_line (8 bytes) - Line number where annotation block ends (0 if unclosed)
Note: offset 24: content (8 bytes) - Pointer to annotation body text
Note: offset 32: is_closed (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if properly closed with @End
Note: offset 40: associated_name (8 bytes) - Pointer to name of associated Process/Type (or 0)

Constant ANNOT_INFO_SIZE as Integer is 48

Note: AnnotationStats memory layout (64 bytes):
Note: offset  0: total_annotations (8 bytes) - Total annotations found
Note: offset  8: reasoning_count (8 bytes) - Count of @Reasoning blocks
Note: offset 16: implementation_count (8 bytes) - Count of @Implementation blocks
Note: offset 24: performance_count (8 bytes) - Count of @Performance_Hints blocks
Note: offset 32: security_count (8 bytes) - Count of @Security_Scope blocks
Note: offset 40: test_cases_count (8 bytes) - Count of @TestCases blocks
Note: offset 48: unclosed_count (8 bytes) - Count of unclosed annotation blocks
Note: offset 56: total_declarations (8 bytes) - Total Process + Type declarations found

Constant ANNOT_STATS_SIZE as Integer is 64

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Scanning
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "scan_for_annotations" takes source as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Scan Runa source for all annotation blocks
    Note: Finds @Reasoning, @Implementation, @Performance_Hints, @Security_Scope, @TestCases
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList of AnnotationInfo pointers, or 0 on failure

    If source is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] Cannot scan: source is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] Cannot scan: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let annotations be arraylist_create(128, 8, arena)
    If annotations is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_len be string_length(source)
    Let pos be 0
    Let line_number be 1

    While pos is less than source_len:
        Let line_start be pos
        Let line_end be string_index_of_from(source, 10, pos)
        If line_end is less than 0:
            Set line_end to source_len
        End If

        Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
        Let line be string_substring(source, line_start, line_len, arena)

        If line is not equal to 0:
            Let trimmed be string_trim(line, arena)
            If trimmed is not equal to 0:
                Note: Check for annotation block starts
                Let annot_type be ANNOT_UNKNOWN

                Let is_reasoning be string_starts_with(trimmed, "@Reasoning")
                If is_reasoning is equal to 1:
                    Set annot_type to ANNOT_REASONING
                End If

                Let is_implementation be string_starts_with(trimmed, "@Implementation")
                If is_implementation is equal to 1:
                    Set annot_type to ANNOT_IMPLEMENTATION
                End If

                Let is_perf be string_starts_with(trimmed, "@Performance_Hints")
                If is_perf is equal to 1:
                    Set annot_type to ANNOT_PERFORMANCE_HINTS
                End If

                Let is_security be string_starts_with(trimmed, "@Security_Scope")
                If is_security is equal to 1:
                    Set annot_type to ANNOT_SECURITY_SCOPE
                End If

                Let is_test be string_starts_with(trimmed, "@TestCases")
                If is_test is equal to 1:
                    Set annot_type to ANNOT_TEST_CASES
                End If

                Note: If we found an annotation start, create an info entry
                If annot_type is not equal to ANNOT_UNKNOWN:
                    Let info be arena_allocate(arena, ANNOT_INFO_SIZE, 8)
                    If info is not equal to 0:
                        memory_zero(info, ANNOT_INFO_SIZE)
                        memory_set_integer(info, 0, annot_type)
                        memory_set_integer(info, 8, line_number)
                        memory_set_integer(info, 32, 0)  Note: Not yet closed

                        Note: Determine the expected end marker
                        Let end_marker be 0
                        If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_REASONING:
                            Set end_marker to "@End Reasoning"
                        End If
                        If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_IMPLEMENTATION:
                            Set end_marker to "@End Implementation"
                        End If
                        If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_PERFORMANCE_HINTS:
                            Set end_marker to "@End Performance_Hints"
                        End If
                        If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_SECURITY_SCOPE:
                            Set end_marker to "@End Security_Scope"
                        End If
                        If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_TEST_CASES:
                            Set end_marker to "@End TestCases"
                        End If

                        Note: Scan ahead for the end marker
                        Let content_text be string_duplicate("", arena)
                        Let scan_pos be line_end plus 1
                        Let scan_line be line_number plus 1
                        Let found_end be 0

                        While scan_pos is less than source_len:
                            Let scan_line_start be scan_pos
                            Let scan_line_end be string_index_of_from(source, 10, scan_pos)
                            If scan_line_end is less than 0:
                                Set scan_line_end to source_len
                            End If

                            Let scan_line_len be scan_line_end minus scan_line_start
                            Let scan_line_text be string_substring(source, scan_line_start, scan_line_len, arena)

                            If scan_line_text is not equal to 0:
                                Let scan_trimmed be string_trim(scan_line_text, arena)
                                If scan_trimmed is not equal to 0:
                                    Note: Check for end marker
                                    If end_marker is not equal to 0:
                                        Let has_end be string_starts_with(scan_trimmed, end_marker)
                                        If has_end is equal to 1:
                                            memory_set_integer(info, 16, scan_line)
                                            memory_set_integer(info, 32, 1)  Note: Properly closed
                                            Set found_end to 1
                                            Set scan_pos to source_len  Note: Exit scan loop
                                        Otherwise:
                                            Note: Append to content
                                            Let with_line be string_concat(content_text, scan_line_text)
                                            Let with_nl be string_concat(with_line, "\n")
                                            deallocate(with_line)
                                            Set content_text to string_duplicate(with_nl, arena)
                                            deallocate(with_nl)
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If

                            Set scan_pos to scan_line_end plus 1
                            Set scan_line to scan_line plus 1
                        End While

                        memory_set_pointer(info, 24, content_text)
                        arraylist_append(annotations, info)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set pos to line_end plus 1
        Set line_number to line_number plus 1
    End While

    Return annotations
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Annotation Validation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "validate_annotations" takes annotations as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Validate all annotation blocks for structural correctness
    Note: Checks: matching @End closers, non-empty content
    Note: Returns number of validation errors found

    If annotations is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be arraylist_length(annotations)
    Let errors be 0
    Let idx be 0

    While idx is less than count:
        Let annot_ptr be arraylist_get(annotations, idx)
        If annot_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let info be memory_get_pointer(annot_ptr, 0)
            If info is not equal to 0:
                Let annot_type be memory_get_integer(info, 0)
                Let start_line be memory_get_integer(info, 8)
                Let is_closed be memory_get_integer(info, 32)

                Note: Check for unclosed annotation blocks
                If is_closed is equal to 0:
                    Let type_name be annotation_type_name(annot_type, arena)
                    Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] Unclosed @", type_name)
                    Let err_msg2 be string_concat(err_msg, " block starting at line ")
                    deallocate(err_msg)
                    Let line_str be integer_to_string(start_line, arena)
                    Let err_msg3 be string_concat(err_msg2, line_str)
                    deallocate(err_msg2)
                    Alert err_msg3
                    deallocate(err_msg3)
                    Set errors to errors plus 1
                End If

                Note: Check for empty annotation content
                Let content be memory_get_pointer(info, 24)
                If content is not equal to 0:
                    Let content_trimmed be string_trim(content, arena)
                    If content_trimmed is not equal to 0:
                        Let content_len be string_length(content_trimmed)
                        If content_len is equal to 0:
                            Set type_name to annotation_type_name(annot_type, arena)
                            Let warn_msg be string_concat("[RUNAANNOTATE WARNING] Empty @", type_name)
                            Let warn_msg2 be string_concat(warn_msg, " block at line ")
                            deallocate(warn_msg)
                            Set line_str to integer_to_string(start_line, arena)
                            Let warn_msg3 be string_concat(warn_msg2, line_str)
                            deallocate(warn_msg2)
                            Alert warn_msg3
                            deallocate(warn_msg3)
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return errors
End Process

Process called "annotation_type_name" takes annot_type as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return human-readable name for an annotation type constant
    If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_REASONING:
        Return string_duplicate("Reasoning", arena)
    End If
    If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_IMPLEMENTATION:
        Return string_duplicate("Implementation", arena)
    End If
    If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_PERFORMANCE_HINTS:
        Return string_duplicate("Performance_Hints", arena)
    End If
    If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_SECURITY_SCOPE:
        Return string_duplicate("Security_Scope", arena)
    End If
    If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_TEST_CASES:
        Return string_duplicate("TestCases", arena)
    End If
    Return string_duplicate("Unknown", arena)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Coverage Reporting
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "report_annotation_coverage" takes annotations as Integer, source as Integer, file_path as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compute and display annotation coverage statistics
    Note: Returns 0

    If annotations is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Count annotation types
    Let stats be arena_allocate(arena, ANNOT_STATS_SIZE, 8)
    If stats is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    memory_zero(stats, ANNOT_STATS_SIZE)

    Let count be arraylist_length(annotations)
    memory_set_integer(stats, 0, count)

    Let idx be 0
    Let unclosed be 0
    While idx is less than count:
        Let annot_ptr be arraylist_get(annotations, idx)
        If annot_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let info be memory_get_pointer(annot_ptr, 0)
            If info is not equal to 0:
                Let annot_type be memory_get_integer(info, 0)
                Let is_closed be memory_get_integer(info, 32)

                If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_REASONING:
                    Let c be memory_get_integer(stats, 8)
                    Set c to c plus 1
                    memory_set_integer(stats, 8, c)
                End If
                If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_IMPLEMENTATION:
                    Set c to memory_get_integer(stats, 16)
                    Set c to c plus 1
                    memory_set_integer(stats, 16, c)
                End If
                If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_PERFORMANCE_HINTS:
                    Set c to memory_get_integer(stats, 24)
                    Set c to c plus 1
                    memory_set_integer(stats, 24, c)
                End If
                If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_SECURITY_SCOPE:
                    Set c to memory_get_integer(stats, 32)
                    Set c to c plus 1
                    memory_set_integer(stats, 32, c)
                End If
                If annot_type is equal to ANNOT_TEST_CASES:
                    Set c to memory_get_integer(stats, 40)
                    Set c to c plus 1
                    memory_set_integer(stats, 40, c)
                End If

                If is_closed is equal to 0:
                    Set unclosed to unclosed plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    memory_set_integer(stats, 48, unclosed)

    Note: Count declarations (Process + Type) in source
    Let decl_count be 0
    If source is not equal to 0:
        Let source_len be string_length(source)
        Let scan_pos be 0
        While scan_pos is less than source_len:
            Let line_start be scan_pos
            Let line_end be string_index_of_from(source, 10, scan_pos)
            If line_end is less than 0:
                Set line_end to source_len
            End If
            Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
            Let scan_line be string_substring(source, line_start, line_len, arena)
            If scan_line is not equal to 0:
                Let scan_trimmed be string_trim(scan_line, arena)
                If scan_trimmed is not equal to 0:
                    Let is_proc be string_starts_with(scan_trimmed, "Process called ")
                    If is_proc is equal to 1:
                        Set decl_count to decl_count plus 1
                    End If
                    Let is_type be string_starts_with(scan_trimmed, "Type called ")
                    If is_type is equal to 1:
                        Set decl_count to decl_count plus 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set scan_pos to line_end plus 1
        End While
    End If
    memory_set_integer(stats, 56, decl_count)

    Note: Display report
    Display "=================================================="
    Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] Annotation Coverage Report"
    If file_path is not equal to 0:
        Display "  File: "
        Display file_path
    End If
    Display "=================================================="
    Display "  Total annotations:       "
    Display count
    Display "  @Reasoning blocks:       "
    Display memory_get_integer(stats, 8)
    Display "  @Implementation blocks:  "
    Display memory_get_integer(stats, 16)
    Display "  @Performance_Hints:      "
    Display memory_get_integer(stats, 24)
    Display "  @Security_Scope:         "
    Display memory_get_integer(stats, 32)
    Display "  @TestCases:              "
    Display memory_get_integer(stats, 40)
    Display "  Unclosed blocks:         "
    Display unclosed
    Display "  Total declarations:      "
    Display decl_count

    Note: Coverage percentage
    If decl_count is greater than 0:
        Let coverage be count multiplied by 100
        Let coverage_pct be coverage divided by decl_count
        Display "  Coverage:                "
        Display coverage_pct
        Display "%"
    End If

    Display "=================================================="

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Missing Annotation Suggestions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "suggest_missing_annotations" takes source as Integer, annotations as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Identify Process and Type declarations that lack nearby annotation blocks
    Note: Returns number of suggestions made

    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_len be string_length(source)
    Let suggestions be 0
    Let pos be 0
    Let line_number be 1

    While pos is less than source_len:
        Let line_start be pos
        Let line_end be string_index_of_from(source, 10, pos)
        If line_end is less than 0:
            Set line_end to source_len
        End If

        Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
        Let line be string_substring(source, line_start, line_len, arena)

        If line is not equal to 0:
            Let trimmed be string_trim(line, arena)
            If trimmed is not equal to 0:
                Let is_process be string_starts_with(trimmed, "Process called ")
                Let is_type be string_starts_with(trimmed, "Type called ")

                If is_process is equal to 1:
                    Note: Check if there is an annotation within 10 lines above
                    Let has_nearby_annot be check_nearby_annotation(source, line_start, annotations, arena)
                    If has_nearby_annot is equal to 0:
                        Note: Extract Process name
                        Let first_quote be string_index_of(trimmed, 34)
                        If first_quote is greater than 0:
                            Let second_quote be string_index_of_from(trimmed, 34, first_quote plus 1)
                            If second_quote is greater than first_quote:
                                Let name_len be second_quote minus first_quote minus 1
                                Let proc_name be string_substring(trimmed, first_quote plus 1, name_len, arena)
                                Let suggest_msg be string_concat("[RUNAANNOTATE SUGGEST] Add @Reasoning before Process '", proc_name)
                                Let suggest_msg2 be string_concat(suggest_msg, "' at line ")
                                deallocate(suggest_msg)
                                Let line_str be integer_to_string(line_number, arena)
                                Let suggest_msg3 be string_concat(suggest_msg2, line_str)
                                deallocate(suggest_msg2)
                                Display suggest_msg3
                                deallocate(suggest_msg3)
                                Set suggestions to suggestions plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                If is_type is equal to 1:
                    Set has_nearby_annot to check_nearby_annotation(source, line_start, annotations, arena)
                    If has_nearby_annot is equal to 0:
                        Set first_quote to string_index_of(trimmed, 34)
                        If first_quote is greater than 0:
                            Set second_quote to string_index_of_from(trimmed, 34, first_quote plus 1)
                            If second_quote is greater than first_quote:
                                Set name_len to second_quote minus first_quote minus 1
                                Let type_name be string_substring(trimmed, first_quote plus 1, name_len, arena)
                                Set suggest_msg to string_concat("[RUNAANNOTATE SUGGEST] Add @Reasoning before Type '", type_name)
                                Set suggest_msg2 to string_concat(suggest_msg, "' at line ")
                                deallocate(suggest_msg)
                                Set line_str to integer_to_string(line_number, arena)
                                Set suggest_msg3 to string_concat(suggest_msg2, line_str)
                                deallocate(suggest_msg2)
                                Display suggest_msg3
                                deallocate(suggest_msg3)
                                Set suggestions to suggestions plus 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set pos to line_end plus 1
        Set line_number to line_number plus 1
    End While

    If suggestions is equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] All declarations have nearby annotations"
    Otherwise:
        Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] "
        Display suggestions
        Display " suggestions for missing annotations"
    End If

    Return suggestions
End Process

Process called "check_nearby_annotation" takes source as Integer, decl_pos as Integer, annotations as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if any annotation block's end_line is within 10 lines above decl_pos
    Note: Returns 1 if found, 0 if not

    If annotations is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Convert decl_pos to line number
    Let decl_line be 1
    Let scan_pos be 0
    While scan_pos is less than decl_pos:
        Let ch be string_char_at(source, scan_pos)
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set decl_line to decl_line plus 1
        End If
        Set scan_pos to scan_pos plus 1
    End While

    Note: Check if any annotation's end_line is within [decl_line - 10, decl_line]
    Let count be arraylist_length(annotations)
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than count:
        Let annot_ptr be arraylist_get(annotations, idx)
        If annot_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let info be memory_get_pointer(annot_ptr, 0)
            If info is not equal to 0:
                Let end_line be memory_get_integer(info, 16)
                Let start_line be memory_get_integer(info, 8)
                Let distance be decl_line minus end_line
                If distance is greater than 0:
                    If distance is less than 11:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
                Note: Also check if annotation starts just above
                Let start_distance be decl_line minus start_line
                If start_distance is greater than 0:
                    If start_distance is less than 11:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "run_annotate" takes argc as Integer, argv as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for the RunaAnnotate tool
    Note: Scans, validates, and reports on annotation coverage
    Note: Returns exit code (0 = success, nonzero = issues found)

    If argc is less than 2:
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE] Usage: runa annotate <file_or_directory> [options]"
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE] Options:"
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE]   --validate   Validate annotation block structure"
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE]   --suggest    Suggest missing annotation blocks"
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE]   --verbose    Enable verbose output"
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Let arena be arena_create(131072)
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] Failed to create arena"
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Let target_path be 0
    Let do_validate be 1      Note: Validation is on by default
    Let do_suggest be 0
    Let is_verbose be 0
    Let ptr_size be 8
    Let i be 1

    While i is less than argc:
        Let arg_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
        Let arg_ptr be argv plus arg_offset
        Let arg be memory_get_pointer(arg_ptr, 0)

        If arg is not equal to 0:
            Let is_validate be string_equals(arg, "--validate")
            If is_validate is equal to 1:
                Set do_validate to 1
            Otherwise:
                Let is_suggest be string_equals(arg, "--suggest")
                If is_suggest is equal to 1:
                    Set do_suggest to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let is_verbose_flag be string_equals(arg, "--verbose")
                    If is_verbose_flag is equal to 1:
                        Set is_verbose to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set target_path to arg
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If target_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] No file or directory specified"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Note: Read the source file
    Let source be runtime_read_file(target_path)
    If source is equal to 0:
        Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNAANNOTATE ERROR] Cannot read: ", target_path)
        Alert err_msg
        deallocate(err_msg)
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] Analyzing: "
    Display target_path

    Note: Scan for annotations
    Let annotations be scan_for_annotations(source, arena)
    If annotations is equal to 0:
        deallocate(source)
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Let annot_count be arraylist_length(annotations)
    If is_verbose is equal to 1:
        Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] Found "
        Display annot_count
        Display " annotation blocks"
    End If

    Note: Validate if requested
    Let validation_errors be 0
    If do_validate is equal to 1:
        Set validation_errors to validate_annotations(annotations, arena)
        If validation_errors is greater than 0:
            Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] Validation found "
            Display validation_errors
            Display " error(s)"
        Otherwise:
            Display "[RUNAANNOTATE] All annotations are structurally valid"
        End If
    End If

    Note: Report coverage
    Let coverage_result be report_annotation_coverage(annotations, source, target_path, arena)

    Note: Suggest missing annotations if requested
    Let suggestion_count be 0
    If do_suggest is equal to 1:
        Set suggestion_count to suggest_missing_annotations(source, annotations, arena)
    End If

    deallocate(source)
    arena_destroy(arena)

    If validation_errors is greater than 0:
        Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_ISSUES_FOUND
    End If

    Return ANNOTATE_TOOL_SUCCESS
End Process
